cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a genetic programming approach for data visualisation, which involves evolving models to create high-quality visualisations. This work is related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS) as it involves developing algorithms to process and analyse large datasets. Additionally, the use of genetic programming is related to neural networks (cs.NE) as it involves evolving models through a process of selection and mutation.
